data.value:
Mask mode: select pixels around chosen
diffraction peaks (hkl reflections) for masking;
mutually exclusive with the other mask modes.

Mask mode: mask an annular (donut) ring between
the Start and End radii from the pattern center;
mutually exclusive with other mask modes.

Mask mode: mask a straight band (rectangle)
defined by direction, band width and angle;
mutually exclusive with other mask modes.

Direction preset for the band mask
(Top/Bottom/Right/Left/Vertical/Horizontal/Free);
presets fix the angle, Free lets you enter it manually.

On-screen display resolution in mm/pixel;
sets the zoom factor (monitor mm/pixel ÷
image mm/pixel) of the displayed pattern.

List of reflection indices (hkl);
check the peaks whose surrounding ring
area you want to select for masking.

Enables manual setup of the initial background;
activates the A/H/R sliders to define a
starting background ring before refinement.

Direction preset for the band mask
(Top/Bottom/Right/Left/Vertical/Horizontal/Free);
Free lets you enter the angle manually.
